biography:
Everyone has a story to tell. 
#ShotoniPhone

relatedProfiles.full_name: A N A   D E   A R M A S

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Commissioned by Apple. A peek behind the scenes as Michel Gondry turns a carton of eggs into a dozen pieces of cinema with #iPhone13Pro 🥚 “I like to start with something very trivial and mundane, and find a way to get magic out of it.” #ShotoniPhone by Michel Gondry. @michelgondry

Follow @apple to see more.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Shot on iPhone 13 in Cinematic mode
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Commissioned by Apple. One missing painting. Six Suspects. Watch Whodunnit, shot entirely in Cinematic mode on the new #iPhone13.

#ShotoniPhone by JB Braud @jbbraud

latestIgtvVideos.title: Window to the Soul
latestIgtvVideos.caption: Commissioned by Apple. “I came up with the idea for my film in a nightmare. I always get my ideas from nightmares. It sounds a bit grim, but it’s not. I just think about what could be happening in a different universe.” #ShotoniPhone by AhaNah C. @vio.waxdrops, Student.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Our Light Shines Through the Dark
latestIgtvVideos.caption: Commissioned by Apple. “I want to see a joyful piece with black men in it because we’re seeing way too much pain in the media and the news. I wanted to create something that would be a much-needed pause from everything that’s happening. I want joy.” #ShotoniPhone by Ciara Z. @ciara.zo, Student.

latestIgtvVideos.title: RobaLuna
latestIgtvVideos.caption: Commissioned by Apple. “Making this film was a fantastic feeling. I don’t care about anything else in the world. This is what I want to do.” #ShotoniPhone by Guillermo M., Student.

latestIgtvVideos.title: The Take
latestIgtvVideos.caption: Commissioned by Apple. “There’s no excuse for anybody not to be making films at this point. It’s a way people can tell their stories and keep them living forever.” #ShotoniPhone by Niko B. @mylifeismundane, Student.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Experiments V: Dark Universe
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Commissioned by Apple. “We wanted to push the #iPhone12Pro with its Dolby Vision and low-light recording capabilities to the limit.”

#ShotoniPhone 12 Pro by Donghoon J. and James T. of @InciteDesign. 

Music: “RADIANCE” by LORN. 

Head to Stories to see how it was made.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Apple is taking action to fight systemic racism.
latestIgtvVideos.caption: “The unfinished work of racial justice and equality call us all to account. Things must change, and Apple's committed to being a force for that change. Today, I'm proud to announce Apple’s Racial Equity and Justice Initiative, with a $100 million commitment.” Tim Cook

latestIgtvVideos.title: Mobile to Museum
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Shawn Theodore is a photographer who has been working to preserve the culture of local neighborhoods that are disappearing fast due to gentrification.
Shawn explains his creative process and the drive to take visual archives from the mobile environment to within fine art institutions.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Water + Light
latestIgtvVideos.caption: Photographer Christy Lee Rogers shoots under water to create photographic works that push the possibilities of movement, color and light.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Gaucha Del Jujuy
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Commissioned by Apple. Gaucha, the female gauchos of Argentina command respect through their leadership and preservation of culture in their communities. This is the story of Julia Lamas. Shot on iPhone 11.

Directors: Martin Reigel and Marco Vernaschi.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Laydown Photography
latestIgtvVideos.caption: Jim Golden is a pioneer of laydown photography. From clothing to analog equipment, Jim takes us through the process of balancing color and composition in his creations.

latestPosts.caption:
Commissioned by Apple. Music moves tradition.

Ratoh Jaroe, with its Acehnese dance and rhythms, is paired with modern music to create a unique Indonesian expression.

“The more I worked with Bang Dek Gam, Kasimyn, and Mas Gatut, the more ‘tradition’ started to feel less like the past—and more like something alive, shifting, leading us to somewhere new.” #ShotoniPhone by Agung Pambudi @agungpambudi_

Music by Kasimyn @kasimyn
Choreography by Bang Dek Gam @king_of_ratoh_jaroe
Photography by Mas Gatut @toet_barra

Sea you later. #ShotoniPhone by Ryan P. @ryanpernofski

Waterproof case used.

Music: ‘MLR’ by @matthewdavidmcq

In the shadows. #ShotoniPhone by @tommiviitala

“Light and shadows have always fascinated me, and I often look for subjects accordingly.” - Tommi V.

latestPosts.caption:
“My queerness has not been easy but it brought me closer to myself, my purpose, and my art.”
1. Emerald Vysions @emerald___vysions

“I am the happiest when I get to create. I want to set an example for those who are trying to find their way.”
2. Param G. @parambanana

“Find the purest form of yourself and let that guide you through this life. Having this understanding of myself has allowed me to nourish my voice within my work.”
3. Lauren W. @laurenwithrow

“Freedom means being myself. I felt most free during the first Pride I participated in—it was like breathing in full color for the first time.”
4. Elif T. @eliftekneci

“My queer identity is deeply intertwined in everything I do and that’s what makes me unique.”
5. Brianna B. @briannablank

“Performing gives me the freedom to follow my instincts and heal a younger version of myself.”
6. Justin W. @djdumpling

Celebrating Pride #ShotoniPhone

Music: ‘FUN!’ by @iamkucka
Hold your horses. #ShotoniPhone by Ozan S. @ozansihay
